WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.889 --> 00:00:44.053
Letters From Iwo Jima

2
00:00:54.170 --> 00:00:57.833
IWO JIMA

3
00:02:08.978 --> 00:02:12.470
How did those soldiers ever manage
to dig out these tunnels?

4
00:02:13.349 --> 00:02:14.748
Let's get a rotation in here.

5
00:02:14.918 --> 00:02:16.818
Hey. I found something!

6
00:02:28.898 --> 00:02:31.662
IWO JIMA
1944

7
00:02:31.835 --> 00:02:32.927
Hanako...

8
00:02:33.903 --> 00:02:35.837
We soldiers dig.

9
00:02:36.339 --> 00:02:39.001
We dig all day.

10
00:02:41.010 --> 00:02:43.069
This is the hole that we will fight...

11
00:02:43.880 --> 00:02:45.609
and die in.

12
00:02:47.951 --> 00:02:49.418
Hanako...

13
00:02:49.953 --> 00:02:53.218
am I digging my own grave?

14
00:03:26.956 --> 00:03:30.483
Today. I head for the post
where my men await.

15
00:03:31.394 --> 00:03:35.592
I am determined to serve
and give my life for my country.

16
00:03:36.733 --> 00:03:39.258
I believe I have organized
everything at home...

17
00:03:39.435 --> 00:03:44.065
but I am sorry I wasn't able to attend
to the kitchen floor before I left.

18
00:03:44.741 --> 00:03:46.504
I had all the intention...

19
00:03:46.676 --> 00:03:49.008
but had to leave
without having the time...

20
00:03:49.445 --> 00:03:51.504
and I am still worried about it.

21
00:03:51.781 --> 00:03:54.909
So make sure to have
Taro take care of it promptly.

22
00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:04.949
Damn this island!
The Americans can have it.

23
00:04:07.430 --> 00:04:08.761
Nothing grows here.

24
00:04:09.699 --> 00:04:14.762
It smells. It's hot. There are too many
damn bugs. and there's no water.

25
00:04:17.040 --> 00:04:20.840
This island is part
of Japan's sacred homeland.

26
00:04:21.144 --> 00:04:23.203
There's nothing sacred about this island.

27
00:04:26.783 --> 00:04:27.943
Saigo.

28
00:04:28.351 --> 00:04:32.185
We should just give the island
to the Americans...

29
00:04:32.455 --> 00:04:33.888
and then we can go home.

30
00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:38.552
Saigo!

31
00:04:40.396 --> 00:04:41.727
What did you say. soldier?

32
00:04:43.399 --> 00:04:46.857
I said if we beat the Americans.
then we can go home.

33
00:04:48.037 --> 00:04:50.164
You there. is that what he said?

34
00:04:51.641 --> 00:04:53.905
Yes. sir.

35
00:06:16.759 --> 00:06:17.817
I'm Kuribayashi.

36
00:06:18.061 --> 00:06:20.723
Welcome. General.
I am Admiral Ohsugi.

37
00:06:21.097 --> 00:06:23.429
How long have you been
waiting here for me?

38
00:06:24.567 --> 00:06:25.932
Three hours. sir.

39
00:06:26.102 --> 00:06:27.433
Sorry to hear that.

40
00:06:27.637 --> 00:06:32.165
They wouldn't allow me to wire my arrival
after what happened to Admiral Yamamoto.

41
00:06:32.442 --> 00:06:33.568
I understand. sir.

42
00:06:33.810 --> 00:06:35.675
This is my aide. Lieutenant Fujita.

43
00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:38.803
What's the matter. Admiral?
You don't look very well.

44
00:06:39.015 --> 00:06:42.348
It's nothing. sir. The water
doesn't agree with me here.

45
00:06:42.518 --> 00:06:44.008
Sorry to hear that.

46
00:06:44.687 --> 00:06:46.177
This way to your quarters.

47
00:06:46.489 --> 00:06:49.083
Admiral. I want to make a round
of the island first.

48
00:06:49.292 --> 00:06:51.317
Shall I fetch a vehicle?

49
00:06:51.494 --> 00:06:53.462
No. let's walk.

50
00:06:54.464 --> 00:06:56.091
Walking is good for the health.

51
00:06:56.265 --> 00:06:58.426
It might be just what you need. Ohsugi.

52
00:07:14.350 --> 00:07:16.113
So that's Suribachi.

53
00:07:25.161 --> 00:07:26.219
You unpatriotic...

54
00:07:26.963 --> 00:07:28.294
no-good peasants!

55
00:07:28.731 --> 00:07:29.993
Hey. stop it!

56
00:07:33.736 --> 00:07:34.828
Stand up!

57
00:07:35.838 --> 00:07:37.203
What are you doing?

58
00:07:39.909 --> 00:07:41.240
These soldiers...

59
00:07:44.113 --> 00:07:46.104
were conspiring
with unpatriotic words. sir.

60
00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:48.276
I see.

61
00:07:48.518 --> 00:07:51.146
And. Captain. do you have
such an excess of soldiers...

62
00:07:51.320 --> 00:07:53.948
that you could put two
of them out of commission?

63
00:07:54.857 --> 00:07:56.051
No. sir.

64
00:07:56.993 --> 00:07:58.620
Then stop beating them.

65
00:07:58.995 --> 00:08:01.293
Deny their lunch rations instead.

66
00:08:01.831 --> 00:08:05.528
A good captain uses his brain.
not just his whip.

67
00:08:10.506 --> 00:08:12.235
What is all this?

68
00:08:12.875 --> 00:08:14.069
All this?

69
00:08:14.377 --> 00:08:15.674
Trenches. sir.

70
00:08:16.379 --> 00:08:18.142
Why are the men digging trenches here?

71
00:08:18.681 --> 00:08:21.514
This is where the Americans
are expected to land.

72
00:08:23.352 --> 00:08:25.081
Have them stop immediately.

73
00:08:25.888 --> 00:08:27.321
But. General--

74
00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:29.152
And. Captain...

75
00:08:29.992 --> 00:08:31.983
make sure these men get proper breaks.

76
00:08:32.328 --> 00:08:34.762
They look like they're from Mars.

77
00:08:47.510 --> 00:08:48.738
Stop digging!

78
00:09:06.229 --> 00:09:07.560
Just as well.

79
00:09:08.764 --> 00:09:11.597
My stomach has been
bothering me anyway.

80
00:09:12.802 --> 00:09:15.032
A toast to General Kuribayashi...

81
00:09:16.739 --> 00:09:18.400
a fine commander.

82
00:09:22.411 --> 00:09:24.072
Better than sake!

83
00:09:24.914 --> 00:09:26.643
I heard he lived in America.

84
00:09:27.883 --> 00:09:30.317
Maybe that's why he
doesn't want us digging trenches.

85
00:09:30.486 --> 00:09:32.215
Maybe he likes Americans.

86
00:09:32.455 --> 00:09:36.050
No. stupid.
He studied the Americans.

87
00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:40.927
So now he knows how to beat them.

88
00:09:42.632 --> 00:09:44.429
I heard from someone in the 204th...

89
00:09:45.167 --> 00:09:49.729
that another general was
supposed to command the island...

90
00:09:50.439 --> 00:09:53.567
but he didn't want the job.

91
00:09:55.011 --> 00:09:59.072
So Premier Tojo gave it
to Kuribayashi instead.

92
00:10:00.449 --> 00:10:04.351
Nozaki. you hear a lot of things...

93
00:10:05.788 --> 00:10:07.949
but your ears are full of wax!

94
00:10:09.625 --> 00:10:13.652
Anyway. you can't trust anyone
from the 204th.

95
00:10:13.829 --> 00:10:15.694
They're part of the Navy.

96
00:10:16.032 --> 00:10:19.024
I think this Kuribayashi
must be a superb general.

97
00:10:19.602 --> 00:10:20.796
Look...

98
00:10:21.537 --> 00:10:26.839
we're not digging those damn trenches
in the sand anymore. are we?

99
00:10:43.359 --> 00:10:46.351
This heat is more than I had anticipated.

100
00:10:51.133 --> 00:10:56.161
This island is bigger than I thought.
I'm exhausted.

101
00:11:03.813 --> 00:11:04.973
Ito. reporting for duty.

102
00:11:05.147 --> 00:11:07.172
Thank you for coming right away.

103
00:11:08.417 --> 00:11:11.045
How much air force
do we have available?

104
00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:13.848
41 Zekes and 13 bombers. sir.

105
00:11:14.023 --> 00:11:15.012
Is that all?

106
00:11:15.191 --> 00:11:19.252
In order to support Saipan.
we lost 66 planes a few days ago.

107
00:11:20.563 --> 00:11:24.897
We will have to rely on support
from the Combined Fleet then.

108
00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:28.861
Is this the current defense plan?

109
00:11:34.577 --> 00:11:37.512
And what about the Army troops?
Where will they be stationed?

110
00:11:40.349 --> 00:11:42.214
I don't know exactly.

111
00:11:42.385 --> 00:11:45.252
They are under independent
command of Colonel Adachi.

112
00:11:45.421 --> 00:11:47.787
You have not coordinated
your plans with the Army?

113
00:11:47.957 --> 00:11:50.721
According to Navy rules.
until the enemy lands--

114
00:11:50.893 --> 00:11:53.794
This is a real war!
You are aware of that. aren't you?

115
00:11:59.935 --> 00:12:01.095
This will not work.

116
00:12:01.270 --> 00:12:03.738
You are concentrating all
your efforts on the beaches.

117
00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:07.337
- Move the artillery to higher ground.
- But. sir. we just had them...

118
00:12:07.510 --> 00:12:09.102
moved down to the beaches.

119
00:12:09.278 --> 00:12:10.745
Well. move them back.

120
00:12:13.115 --> 00:12:15.709
Coordinate with the Army
and have them start immediately.

121
00:12:15.885 --> 00:12:18.945
Fortifications at Suribachi are the priority.

122
00:12:19.422 --> 00:12:20.719
I'm going to walk some more.

123
00:12:20.923 --> 00:12:23.790
- It's pitch black out there. sir.
- I know.

124
00:12:34.804 --> 00:12:36.294
This one is trouble.

125
00:12:38.274 --> 00:12:41.607
Army commanders usually are. sir.

126
00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:25.685
Another letter?

127
00:13:25.888 --> 00:13:28.982
You know that the mail only goes out
when there's a boat available?

128
00:13:29.458 --> 00:13:30.857
I have a lot of family.

129
00:13:31.393 --> 00:13:34.191
Then how come all your letters
are addressed to your wife?

130
00:13:35.798 --> 00:13:36.958
Nosey!

131
00:13:37.166 --> 00:13:38.793
Here. let me do you a favor.

132
00:13:39.335 --> 00:13:42.498
Otherwise. your letters
will never make it through.

133
00:13:43.672 --> 00:13:45.367
Hey. what are you doing?

134
00:13:45.808 --> 00:13:49.244
I used to work at the censorship office
in Tokyo before I was transferred.

135
00:13:50.212 --> 00:13:52.009
You mean demoted.

136
00:13:52.982 --> 00:13:56.509
"To Hanako: We soldiers dig.
We dig all day."

137
00:13:56.719 --> 00:13:59.381
No. no. no. This will never pass.

138
00:14:01.390 --> 00:14:02.982
Give me that back!

139
00:14:11.767 --> 00:14:16.170
There. You'll thank me
for this later. Saigo.

140
00:14:20.009 --> 00:14:21.169
Next!

141
00:14:27.683 --> 00:14:28.911
Good!

142
00:14:55.477 --> 00:14:57.069
Are you blind?

143
00:14:58.614 --> 00:15:00.411
Can't you see the target?

144
00:15:01.750 --> 00:15:05.083
Even my six-year-old could
shoot better than you do.

145
00:15:06.322 --> 00:15:07.448
Do it again!

146
00:15:13.495 --> 00:15:16.987
You're an embarrassment!
You call yourself an Imperial soldier?

147
00:15:18.934 --> 00:15:22.495
Tonight you will clean the boots
of your entire troop.

148
00:15:22.671 --> 00:15:23.763
Go to the rear!

149
00:15:26.275 --> 00:15:29.904
They should learn to clean their guns
properly. rather than their boots.

150
00:16:05.481 --> 00:16:07.312
What are those tanks doing here?

151
00:16:07.650 --> 00:16:11.643
Those are out of commission. sir.
They are waiting for parts.

152
00:16:11.854 --> 00:16:14.482
- For how long?
- About a month. sir.

153
00:16:34.343 --> 00:16:37.710
Taro. America is filled with cars.

154
00:16:38.847 --> 00:16:43.011
I have to be very careful
when I cross the street...

155
00:16:43.852 --> 00:16:46.412
there are so many cars everywhere.

156
00:16:47.489 --> 00:16:51.482
Taro. are you behaving yourself
and listening to your mother?

157
00:16:52.227 --> 00:16:53.854
I miss you.

158
00:17:03.906 --> 00:17:07.171
These civilians need to be
evacuated as soon as possible.

159
00:17:08.377 --> 00:17:10.106
Yes. sir.

160
00:18:11.440 --> 00:18:12.464
Hanako...

161
00:18:13.408 --> 00:18:15.308
we have a celebrity here.

162
00:18:15.911 --> 00:18:19.244
Baron Nishi. the Olympic gold medalist
in horse jumping.

163
00:18:20.649 --> 00:18:23.447
He will lead the 26th tank regiment...

164
00:18:24.119 --> 00:18:26.986
and has just arrived from Tokyo.

165
00:18:41.970 --> 00:18:46.134
Nishi is very handsome. and there are
rumors of his womanizing skills.

166
00:18:47.376 --> 00:18:51.642
But there are no women
left on the island to woo.

167
00:19:18.006 --> 00:19:21.032
Lieutenant Colonel Nishi!
You brought your horse.

168
00:19:21.643 --> 00:19:22.803
From Chichi Jima.

169
00:19:28.884 --> 00:19:30.977
I used to be a cavalryman myself.
you know.

170
00:19:31.153 --> 00:19:33.212
Of course. I know.

171
00:19:33.488 --> 00:19:36.889
I've been looking forward
to serving under you.

172
00:19:37.492 --> 00:19:39.983
One who understands horses
the way I do.

173
00:19:40.162 --> 00:19:44.326
When we used to ride horses
through the battlefield...

174
00:19:44.499 --> 00:19:46.364
those were the good old days...

175
00:19:47.769 --> 00:19:49.828
not like these mechanized contraptions.

176
00:19:51.173 --> 00:19:53.368
I could send for another horse...

177
00:19:54.243 --> 00:19:55.733
and we could ride together.

178
00:19:55.911 --> 00:19:57.572
I'm afraid my riding days are over.

179
00:19:59.181 --> 00:20:03.948
But tell me about this famous horse
of yours that you won the Olympics with.

180
00:20:04.853 --> 00:20:06.184
My stallion. Uranus.

181
00:20:17.566 --> 00:20:20.694
Oh. yes. this horse has a fine back.

182
00:20:24.273 --> 00:20:26.241
I bought him in Italy.

183
00:20:27.075 --> 00:20:29.066
They were happy to get rid of him.

184
00:20:29.244 --> 00:20:31.974
He was such a wild horse.

185
00:20:32.981 --> 00:20:37.281
No one could tame the beast.
but I told them...

186
00:20:37.452 --> 00:20:39.386
such a headstrong horse...

187
00:20:39.788 --> 00:20:43.155
is a perfect match for me.

188
00:20:47.562 --> 00:20:50.224
Come dine with me tonight.
I feel like having a drink.

189
00:20:51.133 --> 00:20:52.623
I think that can be arranged.

190
00:21:02.344 --> 00:21:04.778
How did you manage to get
the Johnnie Walker?

191
00:21:05.447 --> 00:21:07.176
I drank some already.

192
00:21:13.522 --> 00:21:16.320
I'm sorry. This is all we have.

193
00:21:16.491 --> 00:21:18.618
That's fine. as long as we have this.

194
00:21:22.931 --> 00:21:24.762
What is this empty plate?

195
00:21:25.934 --> 00:21:30.428
I have told our cook that all officers will
have the same rations and food as our men.

196
00:21:30.605 --> 00:21:33.665
I'm sorry. but serving three dishes
is regulation.

197
00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:38.441
Oh. but of course we have the right to be
served more than three dishes per meal.

198
00:21:38.613 --> 00:21:39.841
You're absolutely right.

199
00:21:50.993 --> 00:21:52.824
When you think about it...

200
00:21:53.195 --> 00:21:57.495
it is regrettable that most of the
Combined Fleet was destroyed.

201
00:21:59.067 --> 00:22:00.830
We still have some battleships left...

202
00:22:01.003 --> 00:22:05.997
but we have very little striking power
from the air or sea.

203
00:22:07.142 --> 00:22:08.632
Nishi. what do you mean?

204
00:22:11.980 --> 00:22:16.576
So you have not heard about
the Mariana battle?

205
00:22:17.686 --> 00:22:22.680
Admiral Ozawa's carrier and boat planes
were destroyed.

206
00:22:25.260 --> 00:22:26.659
The Imperial headquarters...

207
00:22:27.329 --> 00:22:30.196
is deceiving not just the people.
but us as well.

208
00:22:30.599 --> 00:22:33.363
If you want my honest opinion. General...

209
00:22:35.070 --> 00:22:37.004
the best thing to do...

210
00:22:37.839 --> 00:22:42.367
would be to sink the island
to the bottom of the sea.

211
00:22:44.846 --> 00:22:46.711
And yet. you still came?

212
00:22:49.885 --> 00:22:50.943
Well...

213
00:22:51.386 --> 00:22:56.380
I figured your men were going to need
all the tanks that I could bring.

214
00:23:45.340 --> 00:23:46.807
This must be it.

215
00:23:47.209 --> 00:23:49.177
Yes. the enemy must land here.

216
00:23:54.649 --> 00:23:55.707
Run!

217
00:23:56.785 --> 00:23:58.377
Like you were one of the Americans!

218
00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:00.520
Go on! Which direction would you take?

219
00:24:29.417 --> 00:24:30.645
Hey...

220
00:24:31.753 --> 00:24:33.846
I think your general has gone mad.

221
00:24:37.826 --> 00:24:39.555
Look at the gun he has.

222
00:24:44.166 --> 00:24:47.158
He probably took it
from a dead American.

223
00:24:48.270 --> 00:24:49.703
Maybe.

224
00:24:57.779 --> 00:24:59.110
Break time is over.

225
00:24:59.848 --> 00:25:01.076
Back to work!

226
00:25:05.754 --> 00:25:07.449
Are you all right. Kashiwara?

227
00:25:08.056 --> 00:25:09.683
You look pale.

228
00:25:11.459 --> 00:25:13.552
I'm fine. It's just the damn water.

229
00:25:14.262 --> 00:25:18.062
But... I... really... need to go.

230
00:25:37.485 --> 00:25:39.715
There will be a major change
in our strategy.

231
00:25:40.388 --> 00:25:45.121
We will dig caves in the Motoyama.
Higashiyama. and Suribachi-yama areas.

232
00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:50.063
We will build these underground
fortifications. and fight to the end.

233
00:25:50.365 --> 00:25:53.562
- What about the beach defenses. sir?
- Not needed.

234
00:25:55.003 --> 00:25:58.734
But. sir. the beach trenches
are our first line of defense.

235
00:25:58.907 --> 00:26:02.274
Without the beach trenches.
how do you expect us to win?

236
00:26:02.444 --> 00:26:07.438
Hayashi. do you know how many cars
America produces in a year?

237
00:26:07.616 --> 00:26:08.776
Five million.

238
00:26:09.251 --> 00:26:12.311
The Americans' technological advancements
cannot be underestimated.

239
00:26:12.487 --> 00:26:15.285
They will cross the beaches eventually.

240
00:26:16.858 --> 00:26:19.383
If we waste our soldiers there.
there is no hope for victory.

241
00:26:19.561 --> 00:26:21.324
It is inevitable that men will die...

242
00:26:21.930 --> 00:26:25.161
but I never heard of an island operation
without beach fortifications.

243
00:26:25.333 --> 00:26:28.962
General. it will be a futile waste of time
to start digging tunnels now.

244
00:26:29.137 --> 00:26:30.764
We should force the enemy
near the island...

245
00:26:30.939 --> 00:26:33.100
and launch a pincer drive
from the sea and air.

246
00:26:33.275 --> 00:26:35.641
I agree. That makes the most sense.

247
00:26:35.844 --> 00:26:36.936
Ohsugi...

248
00:26:37.979 --> 00:26:39.674
doesn't the Navy know?

249
00:26:43.718 --> 00:26:47.210
The Combined Fleet has been completely
destroyed off the Marianas.

250
00:26:47.455 --> 00:26:49.514
The island is now isolated.

251
00:26:55.096 --> 00:26:58.793
What's more. I received a new order from
the Imperial headquarters this morning.

252
00:26:59.167 --> 00:27:03.365
The remaining fighter planes are to be
sent back to Tokyo to defend the mainland.

253
00:27:03.538 --> 00:27:06.564
Outrageous! How are we to fight?

254
00:27:10.345 --> 00:27:14.247
We do not have time for discussion.
We should head back.

255
00:27:47.248 --> 00:27:48.408
Dear Mother...

256
00:27:50.051 --> 00:27:53.282
I have been commissioned
to a new troop today.

257
00:27:55.056 --> 00:27:58.548
I cannot talk about this transfer now.

258
00:28:00.061 --> 00:28:01.858
Take good care of yourself.

259
00:28:16.044 --> 00:28:17.375
Look at this picture.

260
00:28:20.615 --> 00:28:22.310
That's some fancy castle.

261
00:28:23.618 --> 00:28:26.280
You know who this castle was built for?

262
00:28:27.122 --> 00:28:28.919
Someone who was already dead.

263
00:28:30.959 --> 00:28:33.484
They must have had
a lot of money back then...

264
00:28:34.028 --> 00:28:36.121
to build a castle like that
for a dead person.

265
00:28:37.766 --> 00:28:39.961
Why are you reading that book anyway?

266
00:28:40.568 --> 00:28:43.264
We're never going to war over there.

267
00:28:44.472 --> 00:28:47.532
We'll be lucky if we even get
a hole in the ground when we're dead.

268
00:28:48.276 --> 00:28:50.267
Don't talk about that. It's bad luck.

269
00:28:55.950 --> 00:28:57.747
Is this the 312th?

270
00:28:58.086 --> 00:28:59.485
That's right.

271
00:29:00.355 --> 00:29:02.949
I'm Nozaki. This is Saigo.

272
00:29:05.593 --> 00:29:08.289
Shimizu. you can put your bedroll there.

273
00:29:12.767 --> 00:29:14.632
There's an empty space in the back.

274
00:29:16.271 --> 00:29:17.499
Don't mind him.

275
00:29:18.773 --> 00:29:22.209
His friend Kashiwara just died.

276
00:29:23.111 --> 00:29:24.874
That used to be his spot.

277
00:29:32.554 --> 00:29:34.488
But we are all going to die.

278
00:29:35.290 --> 00:29:37.281
That's the plan. isn't it?

279
00:29:39.527 --> 00:29:41.518
For our country. it is an honor.

280
00:29:43.832 --> 00:29:46.130
Kashiwara died of honorable dysentery.

281
00:29:47.569 --> 00:29:50.231
Shimizu. where are you from?

282
00:29:52.574 --> 00:29:53.836
Kanagawa-ken.

283
00:29:55.543 --> 00:29:57.568
Ozawa is from there. aren't you?

284
00:29:58.646 --> 00:29:59.977
That's right.

285
00:30:03.918 --> 00:30:05.545
Where were you trained?

286
00:30:06.321 --> 00:30:09.256
Maybe we were at the same school?

287
00:30:10.325 --> 00:30:11.383
No.

288
00:30:12.093 --> 00:30:14.254
I trained in Tokyo.

289
00:30:14.696 --> 00:30:17.028
I trained in Tokyo. too. Where?

290
00:30:24.439 --> 00:30:26.600
The Koho Kimmu Yoin Yoseijo.

291
00:30:38.386 --> 00:30:39.683
Hey...

292
00:30:41.155 --> 00:30:43.419
why do you think they put
a Kempeitai in our unit?

293
00:30:43.591 --> 00:30:44.956
I don't know.

294
00:30:49.297 --> 00:30:52.460
He's not wearing the white armband.
He's not Kempeitai.

295
00:30:54.269 --> 00:30:56.430
He went to the Kempeitai
military academy.

296
00:30:57.539 --> 00:30:59.473
Maybe he was kicked out.

297
00:31:03.211 --> 00:31:05.372
He acts like a Kempeitai.

298
00:31:09.951 --> 00:31:12.419
Look at his holster.
That's not standard issue.

299
00:31:14.589 --> 00:31:17.922
He's been put here to spy on us.

300
00:31:19.661 --> 00:31:22.152
Why would he spy on us?

301
00:31:23.998 --> 00:31:27.627
Maybe it's those letters
you've been writing.

302
00:31:29.971 --> 00:31:31.563
You should be careful.

303
00:31:58.199 --> 00:32:00.292
Weed soup again?

304
00:32:02.370 --> 00:32:05.862
Kuribayashi is conserving
our food supplies for the battle.

305
00:32:06.774 --> 00:32:10.505
We'll be dead
before the Americans even get here.

306
00:32:12.347 --> 00:32:15.475
And you would think that with all my
war effort contributions...

307
00:32:15.717 --> 00:32:19.312
we should be eating kasutera cakes
or sandwiches.

308
00:32:20.722 --> 00:32:21.882
What?

309
00:32:22.657 --> 00:32:27.890
I ran a bakery in Ohmiya with my wife.

310
00:32:28.329 --> 00:32:30.160
Back when we could still get sugar...

311
00:32:31.633 --> 00:32:36.229
we sold ampan and kasutera cakes.

312
00:32:44.145 --> 00:32:48.047
However. his Kempeitai brethren...

313
00:32:49.083 --> 00:32:51.483
used to come and take
whatever they wanted.

314
00:32:54.856 --> 00:32:56.551
For the war...

315
00:32:58.393 --> 00:33:00.190
For the country...

316
00:33:02.664 --> 00:33:04.222
Why bread?

317
00:33:07.402 --> 00:33:12.704
We ran into those types
at our clothing store as well.

318
00:33:15.043 --> 00:33:17.341
When we started making sandwiches...

319
00:33:18.846 --> 00:33:21.041
they took those. too.

320
00:33:23.117 --> 00:33:26.712
And when we ran out of meat
and just had bread. they still came.

321
00:33:31.893 --> 00:33:36.227
Eventually. they took all of our
baking equipment for the metal...

322
00:33:38.900 --> 00:33:42.028
and we were out of business.

323
00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:47.737
I should have been a fisherman.

324
00:33:51.112 --> 00:33:53.307
It must have been hard on your wife...

325
00:33:56.217 --> 00:33:58.742
without the shop
and without her husband.

326
00:34:32.453 --> 00:34:36.412
Tell them to go away.
We have nothing to sell.

327
00:34:42.463 --> 00:34:46.194
Congratulations! Your husband
is going to war.

328
00:35:00.948 --> 00:35:02.711
Thank you very much.

329
00:35:03.384 --> 00:35:07.218
I'm happy to serve the country.

330
00:35:11.325 --> 00:35:14.817
Prayers for your eternal success at arms.

331
00:35:15.396 --> 00:35:19.856
I beg of you! We have only each other.

332
00:35:23.571 --> 00:35:26.062
This is not the time.

333
00:35:28.142 --> 00:35:32.806
We have all sent our husbands
and sons to war.

334
00:35:33.648 --> 00:35:37.846
We all have to do our part.

335
00:35:41.689 --> 00:35:44.487
At least you'll have a little one
to carry on your name.

336
00:35:57.805 --> 00:36:00.330
I can't eat with you like that.

337
00:36:03.344 --> 00:36:07.644
What am I going to do after you die?

338
00:36:14.021 --> 00:36:16.251
I'm not in the coffin yet.

339
00:36:19.060 --> 00:36:22.826
The men never come home.
not even a soul.

340
00:36:25.600 --> 00:36:27.500
They'll never let you come home.

341
00:36:29.537 --> 00:36:30.936
Don't worry.

342
00:36:33.441 --> 00:36:35.068
And now. with the baby.

343
00:36:58.766 --> 00:37:00.063
Can you hear me?

344
00:37:01.802 --> 00:37:03.099
It's Dad.

345
00:37:06.073 --> 00:37:07.131
Listen.

346
00:37:10.111 --> 00:37:13.808
Don't tell anyone
what I'm telling you now.

347
00:37:16.117 --> 00:37:17.277
It's a secret.

348
00:37:32.500 --> 00:37:33.728
Your dad...

349
00:37:37.571 --> 00:37:39.596
is going to come home for you.

350
00:38:35.863 --> 00:38:37.057
Hurry up!

351
00:38:40.501 --> 00:38:42.025
The enemy approaches!

352
00:38:52.747 --> 00:38:54.146
This is ridiculous!

353
00:38:54.715 --> 00:38:57.013
Why waste time digging these tunnels?

354
00:38:57.685 --> 00:38:59.744
They are all going to die anyway.

355
00:39:00.354 --> 00:39:03.915
At least he conceded
to the pillboxes on the beach.

356
00:39:16.871 --> 00:39:18.566
You wanted to see me. sir?

357
00:39:19.740 --> 00:39:21.264
Care for a drink?

358
00:39:26.747 --> 00:39:29.045
You have been looking
quite pale these days.

359
00:39:32.553 --> 00:39:36.387
It's the water. It has
never agreed with me.

360
00:39:36.791 --> 00:39:38.019
That's not good.

361
00:39:39.560 --> 00:39:42.586
Why don't you go back
to the mainland to recoup?

362
00:39:44.198 --> 00:39:48.362
I have commissioned Admiral Ichimaru
to take your place.

363
00:39:50.071 --> 00:39:52.369
We are wasting time
digging these tunnels.

364
00:39:53.074 --> 00:39:57.204
General. the island won't last
five days without fleet support.

365
00:39:58.779 --> 00:40:01.145
We should fight to the death.

366
00:40:02.583 --> 00:40:06.917
The tunnel-digging may be futile.

367
00:40:07.721 --> 00:40:11.623
Maybe the stand on Iwo will be futile.

368
00:40:12.093 --> 00:40:14.288
Maybe the whole war is futile.

369
00:40:14.462 --> 00:40:16.123
But will you give up then?

370
00:40:16.464 --> 00:40:18.591
We will defend this island
until we are dead!

371
00:40:18.766 --> 00:40:20.996
Until the very last soldier is dead!

372
00:40:21.836 --> 00:40:26.170
If our children can live safely
for one more day...

373
00:40:26.440 --> 00:40:29.568
it would be worth the one more day
that we defend this island!

374
00:40:30.478 --> 00:40:31.672
Ohsugi...

375
00:40:32.279 --> 00:40:36.272
if you have an ounce
of pride left as an officer...

376
00:40:37.151 --> 00:40:38.482
I beg of you...

377
00:40:39.120 --> 00:40:42.248
go back to headquarters
and ask them to send support.

378
00:41:06.981 --> 00:41:10.678
So the rumor is true?
I couldn't believe it.

379
00:41:12.119 --> 00:41:15.953
I'm grateful to be leaving this island.

380
00:41:17.691 --> 00:41:19.682
We may have had our differences...

381
00:41:20.861 --> 00:41:23.728
but I'm truly sorry to see you go.

382
00:41:25.232 --> 00:41:28.395
General Hayashi. it is up to you now.

383
00:41:30.004 --> 00:41:34.873
Kuribayashi belongs behind a desk.
not commanding war.

384
00:41:35.643 --> 00:41:37.008
I understand.

385
00:41:37.344 --> 00:41:40.871
There are many of us
who agree with you. sir.

386
00:41:55.996 --> 00:41:56.985
Listen.

387
00:41:57.498 --> 00:42:01.195
The Americans are likely to land here.

388
00:42:02.703 --> 00:42:05.103
Crossfire positions will be here...

389
00:42:06.273 --> 00:42:07.262
here...

390
00:42:08.409 --> 00:42:09.569
and here.

391
00:42:11.011 --> 00:42:12.273
The fact is...

392
00:42:12.446 --> 00:42:18.749
we are completely
outnumbered in every sector.

393
00:42:20.554 --> 00:42:22.545
But we have a great advantage.

394
00:42:23.557 --> 00:42:26.117
Can anyone tell me what that is?

395
00:42:31.732 --> 00:42:34.724
The Americans are weak-willed
and inferior to Japanese soldiers.

396
00:42:34.902 --> 00:42:36.369
Very good. Shimizu.

397
00:42:37.271 --> 00:42:38.761
Why is that?

398
00:42:39.073 --> 00:42:40.631
They are not as disciplined...

399
00:42:40.808 --> 00:42:43.538
and they let their emotions
interfere with their duty.

400
00:42:43.711 --> 00:42:44.973
That is correct.

401
00:42:48.649 --> 00:42:51.641
Here is the uniform
of an American medic.

402
00:42:53.120 --> 00:42:54.382
He should be your target.

403
00:42:55.222 --> 00:42:59.283
For Americans will risk the lives
of many soldiers to save this one.

404
00:43:00.227 --> 00:43:01.285
Understood?

405
00:43:12.840 --> 00:43:15.775
General. may I speak with you?

406
00:43:18.178 --> 00:43:20.612
Please keep an eye on
Major General Hayashi.

407
00:43:22.850 --> 00:43:25.080
Thank you for your concern. Nishi...

408
00:43:25.419 --> 00:43:28.445
but we don't have any time to waste.

409
00:43:28.789 --> 00:43:32.020
We must think about what
we can do at this moment.

410
00:43:35.329 --> 00:43:36.796
Admiral Ichimaru.

411
00:43:39.967 --> 00:43:41.832
Reporting for duty. sir.

412
00:43:42.836 --> 00:43:44.463
Excuse me.

413
00:43:44.872 --> 00:43:47.466
Thank you for coming
on such short notice.

414
00:45:45.926 --> 00:45:47.086
Jupiter!

415
00:45:49.930 --> 00:45:51.227
Jupiter.

416
00:46:42.483 --> 00:46:43.677
Yamazaki...

417
00:46:44.718 --> 00:46:47.846
what are you doing just
sitting there? Help us--

418
00:47:27.828 --> 00:47:30.661
I think he's writing about us in his reports.

419
00:47:31.865 --> 00:47:33.526
He's just writing a letter.

420
00:47:34.034 --> 00:47:36.901
It's been two months. Nozaki.

421
00:47:38.372 --> 00:47:40.169
He would have reported us by now.

422
00:47:40.340 --> 00:47:42.069
How can you be sure?

423
00:47:50.083 --> 00:47:52.881
Will they ever stop?

424
00:47:53.353 --> 00:47:56.379
Day and night. day and night...

425
00:47:58.759 --> 00:48:00.727
It's driving me crazy!

426
00:48:01.562 --> 00:48:05.931
If the damn Americans
are going to invade...

427
00:48:07.801 --> 00:48:09.769
why don't they hurry up and land?

428
00:48:24.451 --> 00:48:25.748
Tako-Chan...

429
00:48:26.086 --> 00:48:30.079
the four chicks that were born
two months ago have grown so much.

430
00:48:30.557 --> 00:48:34.584
The mother chicken leads them
for food every day...

431
00:48:35.095 --> 00:48:39.259
but they're giving me a hard time. picking
at the vegetable garden I have grown.

432
00:48:44.237 --> 00:48:47.570
The fleet of American ships
has left Saipan.

433
00:48:55.983 --> 00:48:57.644
So they are on their way.

434
00:48:59.286 --> 00:49:01.083
Ready the troops.

435
00:49:36.823 --> 00:49:37.983
Men...

436
00:49:39.326 --> 00:49:42.318
the time has come
to show your true colors.

437
00:49:43.296 --> 00:49:45.628
As a member of the honorable
Imperial Army...

438
00:49:46.366 --> 00:49:48.834
I trust that you will fight with honor.

439
00:49:52.072 --> 00:49:56.031
This island is of utmost importance
to Japan.

440
00:49:57.344 --> 00:49:58.709
Should the island fall...

441
00:50:01.014 --> 00:50:02.675
the enemy...

442
00:50:03.583 --> 00:50:07.679
will use it as their base
to attack our homeland.

443
00:50:09.089 --> 00:50:10.681
For the mainland...

444
00:50:12.159 --> 00:50:13.717
For our homeland...

445
00:50:14.261 --> 00:50:16.695
Until the very last man.

446
00:50:17.564 --> 00:50:20.727
Our duty is to stop the enemy right here.

447
00:50:22.135 --> 00:50:23.602
Not one of you...

448
00:50:24.237 --> 00:50:27.434
is allowed to die until you have killed
10 enemy soldiers.

449
00:50:31.478 --> 00:50:34.845
Do not expect to return home alive.

450
00:50:37.617 --> 00:50:41.451
I will always be in front of you.

451
00:50:50.597 --> 00:50:52.258
Long live the Emperor.

452
00:51:36.343 --> 00:51:39.676
Take care and be well.

453
00:51:41.181 --> 00:51:46.312
I will fight courageously until the end.
in the spirit of Yamato.

454
00:51:47.487 --> 00:51:51.856
My heart will always be with you.

455
00:51:52.893 --> 00:51:54.155
Takeichi.

456
00:52:10.544 --> 00:52:15.948
Every household is assigned a quota
of bag-making for the gunpowder.

457
00:52:16.716 --> 00:52:21.210
I cannot help but get tense when I think
that these will be used in battle.

458
00:52:22.055 --> 00:52:25.047
Taro and Yoko laugh at me for this.

459
00:52:25.959 --> 00:52:29.292
Takako. on evacuation in Nagano.
is also doing well.

460
00:52:30.096 --> 00:52:32.223
I pray for your safety.

461
00:52:33.233 --> 00:52:35.633
Sincerely. Yoshi.

462
00:52:49.549 --> 00:52:51.244
No one can shoot me now.

463
00:52:55.255 --> 00:52:59.487
That's a nice belt.
My wife sent me one. too.

464
00:53:04.231 --> 00:53:08.395
Doesn't look like Mr. Kempeitai
has a thousand-stitch belt. does he?

465
00:53:08.768 --> 00:53:11.259
Maybe he thinks it will clash
with his uniform.

466
00:53:11.438 --> 00:53:13.998
He probably doesn't believe
in superstitions. anyway.

467
00:53:18.945 --> 00:53:21.243
His mother made him one after all.

468
00:53:44.337 --> 00:53:47.500
- Maybe they're trying to sink the island.
- My head hurts.

469
00:53:47.774 --> 00:53:50.766
How many ships do you think
there are out there?

470
00:53:50.944 --> 00:53:54.641
At least 30. Maybe even 50.

471
00:53:54.981 --> 00:53:57.575
- They must be really close.
- I need to take a leak.

472
00:53:57.751 --> 00:54:00.481
Don't go near the sewers.
Dysentery is spreading through there.

473
00:54:00.654 --> 00:54:01.814
Where do I go then?

474
00:54:02.155 --> 00:54:04.146
There is a pot at the end of the cave.

475
00:54:24.511 --> 00:54:26.376
The shit pot is full.

476
00:54:26.680 --> 00:54:28.648
Someone needs to throw it out.

477
00:54:52.205 --> 00:54:54.605
If anything happens to that pot...

478
00:54:56.042 --> 00:55:00.945
you'll be carrying our shit away
with your hands.

479
00:56:07.981 --> 00:56:09.812
Is this some kind of a joke?

480
00:56:10.850 --> 00:56:13.318
Why are you always picking on me?

481
00:56:52.292 --> 00:56:56.752
Thank you. God. I take back
what I said before.

482
00:57:11.478 --> 00:57:13.309
Shall we commence fire?

483
00:57:13.680 --> 00:57:14.772
Not yet.

484
00:57:19.886 --> 00:57:22.480
The men wish to commence firing.

485
00:57:29.996 --> 00:57:31.327
Hold your fire!

486
00:57:34.667 --> 00:57:35.998
Hold your fire!

487
00:57:36.336 --> 00:57:37.667
Hold your fire!

488
00:57:45.712 --> 00:57:48.738
They will take the beach
in no time if we do not resist.

489
00:57:48.915 --> 00:57:50.906
Wait until the beach is full.

490
00:58:13.606 --> 00:58:16.507
Let's go. Commence firing!

491
00:58:22.448 --> 00:58:23.881
Commence firing!

492
00:58:25.018 --> 00:58:26.451
Commence firing!

493
00:59:28.581 --> 00:59:30.606
The guns of the Kitakubo unit
were destroyed.

494
00:59:30.783 --> 00:59:33.115
All the pillbox units on the beach
have been destroyed.

495
00:59:33.286 --> 00:59:35.186
However. all other forces are intact...

496
00:59:35.355 --> 00:59:37.619
and we estimate more than
1.000 enemy casualties.

497
00:59:38.124 --> 00:59:40.524
The pillbox destruction was unavoidable.

498
00:59:40.927 --> 00:59:43.020
Overall. that is good news.

499
00:59:43.296 --> 00:59:45.196
How are the men
holding up at Suribachi?

500
00:59:46.299 --> 00:59:47.664
Forces are intact.

501
00:59:51.437 --> 00:59:52.836
What is the enemy situation?

502
00:59:53.006 --> 00:59:55.998
Approximately 20.000 men and 80 tanks.

503
00:59:56.409 --> 01:00:00.641
There has to be more than that.
They still have men waiting in the boats.

504
01:00:00.847 --> 01:00:03.338
Currently the enemy front extends...

505
01:00:03.816 --> 01:00:06.512
between Suribachi
and the south landing...

506
01:00:07.053 --> 01:00:09.317
and Chidori airfield south.

507
01:00:09.989 --> 01:00:14.187
Just as I thought... Suribachi
and the Motoyama airfield.

508
01:00:15.161 --> 01:00:17.459
They are making a two-pronged attack.

509
01:00:32.812 --> 01:00:35.975
That's not enough! I need more ammo.

510
01:01:01.207 --> 01:01:02.538
Take his place!

511
01:01:02.942 --> 01:01:05.069
- The machine gun is blasted.
- Use your rifle!

512
01:01:07.680 --> 01:01:09.204
Watch out! Imbecile!

513
01:01:10.283 --> 01:01:11.511
I can't rely on you.

514
01:01:11.684 --> 01:01:14.881
Go send a report to Colonel Adachi
that we need another machine gun.

515
01:01:15.288 --> 01:01:16.550
Hurry up!

516
01:01:42.982 --> 01:01:45.246
Colonel Adachi is asking
for reinforcements.

517
01:01:45.618 --> 01:01:49.918
We can't afford to send reinforcements.
Tell him to hold out.

518
01:02:01.481 --> 01:02:02.778
Shoot him!

519
01:02:10.791 --> 01:02:13.123
- What's the matter?
- We're out of bullets!

520
01:02:31.812 --> 01:02:33.803
We are losing Suribachi.

521
01:02:34.648 --> 01:02:38.982
All is lost. Request permission
to lead a suicide mission.

522
01:02:39.486 --> 01:02:42.478
No. You must try to hold them off.

523
01:02:43.223 --> 01:02:47.057
Do what you can to survive
and join forces in the north caves.

524
01:02:47.861 --> 01:02:48.953
But. sir...

525
01:02:49.663 --> 01:02:52.564
I have failed to hold Suribachi.

526
01:02:52.833 --> 01:02:55.734
Permit me to die with honor with my men.

527
01:02:56.069 --> 01:02:57.229
No. Colonel.

528
01:02:57.904 --> 01:02:59.235
This is an order!

529
01:03:04.678 --> 01:03:05.838
Adachi.

530
01:03:08.015 --> 01:03:09.175
Adachi!

531
01:03:22.095 --> 01:03:26.122
Sir. Captain Tanida
requests machine guns.

532
01:03:28.268 --> 01:03:29.565
It's over.

533
01:03:37.711 --> 01:03:38.905
Suicide...

534
01:03:40.280 --> 01:03:42.248
That's the only thing left.

535
01:03:43.183 --> 01:03:44.172
But--

536
01:03:45.519 --> 01:03:48.511
Here. take this to your commander.

537
01:04:33.467 --> 01:04:37.096
I heard General Kuribayashi
order Colonel Adachi to escape.

538
01:04:37.270 --> 01:04:38.294
Quiet!

539
01:04:41.842 --> 01:04:45.107
Escape is the coward's way.

540
01:04:46.279 --> 01:04:47.507
Sit down!

541
01:04:59.659 --> 01:05:00.751
Men...

542
01:05:03.630 --> 01:05:04.688
we are...

543
01:05:07.534 --> 01:05:09.866
honorable soldiers of the Emperor.

544
01:05:13.607 --> 01:05:15.131
Don't ever forget that.

545
01:05:19.312 --> 01:05:21.212
The only way left for us...

546
01:05:23.150 --> 01:05:25.050
is to die with honor.

547
01:05:28.822 --> 01:05:30.312
This is our fate...

548
01:05:31.992 --> 01:05:34.324
to find our place at Yasukuni Shrine.

549
01:05:39.399 --> 01:05:41.060
I'll see you there.

550
01:06:00.854 --> 01:06:02.845
Soldiers. farewell!

551
01:07:58.138 --> 01:07:59.196
Stop!

552
01:08:06.813 --> 01:08:10.374
You should die like an honorable soldier.

553
01:08:11.284 --> 01:08:12.808
Look. Shimizu...

554
01:08:15.555 --> 01:08:18.353
we can still join the troops
in the northern caves.

555
01:08:19.326 --> 01:08:21.988
Our orders are to stay here until death.

556
01:08:22.162 --> 01:08:23.993
I heard General Kuribayashi himself.

557
01:08:25.131 --> 01:08:26.792
That's what he said...

558
01:08:28.635 --> 01:08:29.966
over the radio.

559
01:08:31.404 --> 01:08:32.666
It's true.

560
01:08:36.843 --> 01:08:39.004
We can die here...

561
01:08:40.647 --> 01:08:43.172
or we can continue fighting.

562
01:08:46.586 --> 01:08:49.487
Which would better serve the Emperor?

563
01:08:52.359 --> 01:08:53.849
Which one?

564
01:09:16.049 --> 01:09:17.414
Where does this go?

565
01:09:17.584 --> 01:09:19.882
It will take us closer to Motoyama.

566
01:09:25.959 --> 01:09:27.790
Do you have orders to move back?

567
01:09:29.229 --> 01:09:31.197
Where are the rest of your men?

568
01:09:31.698 --> 01:09:33.029
All dead.

569
01:09:34.567 --> 01:09:36.432
It's the same with us.

570
01:09:44.444 --> 01:09:46.708
There should be an outlet
somewhere near here.

571
01:09:46.913 --> 01:09:48.073
Be quiet!

572
01:10:35.795 --> 01:10:40.630
So you thought you could blow us up.
or burn us alive. did you?

573
01:10:56.316 --> 01:10:58.648
- Have we heard from Suribachi?
- No. sir.

574
01:10:58.818 --> 01:11:00.342
Send a messenger!

575
01:11:08.361 --> 01:11:12.320
Lieutenant Oiso has ordered us
to rendezvous at the east cave.

576
01:11:20.507 --> 01:11:23.476
We will make a run for Motoyama.

577
01:11:24.177 --> 01:11:26.805
There is no cover for two kilometers.

578
01:11:27.547 --> 01:11:30.175
It will be every man for himself.

579
01:11:36.856 --> 01:11:38.687
See you on the other side.

580
01:11:39.359 --> 01:11:43.159
If not on this earth.
then in the next world.

581
01:11:58.111 --> 01:12:00.773
Don't run with the herd.
That's where the enemy will fire.

582
01:12:00.947 --> 01:12:02.175
Stay back.

583
01:12:02.982 --> 01:12:04.347
That's cowardice!

584
01:12:06.286 --> 01:12:09.813
There is no use for a dead soldier.

585
01:12:39.752 --> 01:12:41.913
Wait until the flare is gone.

586
01:13:08.047 --> 01:13:09.776
Crawl forward.

587
01:13:28.268 --> 01:13:29.792
What happened to the messenger?

588
01:13:30.036 --> 01:13:31.435
He never came back.

589
01:13:35.441 --> 01:13:37.033
I will go to Adachi myself.

590
01:13:37.310 --> 01:13:40.438
Motoyama's transmitter
still works. General.

591
01:13:41.681 --> 01:13:43.581
Why not try there. sir?

592
01:14:04.671 --> 01:14:06.662
Sir. these men retreated
from Mt. Suribachi.

593
01:14:13.780 --> 01:14:15.145
What are your names?

594
01:14:15.448 --> 01:14:17.973
Saigo. from the 312th.

595
01:14:18.618 --> 01:14:20.142
Shimizu. reporting for duty.

596
01:14:22.322 --> 01:14:24.313
You escaped from Suribachi?

597
01:14:30.797 --> 01:14:32.822
How dare you!

598
01:14:34.734 --> 01:14:37.669
It was your duty
to stay in your position until death.

599
01:14:39.972 --> 01:14:41.530
You should have died...

600
01:14:42.475 --> 01:14:44.841
with your fellow troop members.

601
01:14:46.045 --> 01:14:49.879
You are both a disgrace.

602
01:14:54.020 --> 01:14:55.510
Get on your knees.

603
01:14:58.157 --> 01:15:00.853
- But. sir--
- I said. get on your knees!

604
01:15:21.080 --> 01:15:23.514
I don't want you to kill
my soldiers needlessly.

605
01:15:25.218 --> 01:15:26.776
Put down your sword.

606
01:15:27.286 --> 01:15:28.617
Put it down!

607
01:15:35.027 --> 01:15:36.551
What's going on here?

608
01:15:38.898 --> 01:15:43.096
These men ran from Suribachi.

609
01:15:45.605 --> 01:15:50.440
Lt. Ito. I gave the order that all survivors
retreat to the north caves.

610
01:15:52.779 --> 01:15:54.440
I am very sorry. General.

611
01:15:56.716 --> 01:15:57.944
It's just...

612
01:15:59.252 --> 01:16:00.719
Suribachi...

613
01:16:03.089 --> 01:16:04.488
has fallen.

614
01:16:25.812 --> 01:16:27.473
Now that Suribachi has been taken...

615
01:16:27.647 --> 01:16:30.047
the enemy will maneuver all forces
onto the hillside.

616
01:16:30.216 --> 01:16:32.241
We must move
our command center north. sir.

617
01:16:38.624 --> 01:16:39.750
Ito...

618
01:16:41.894 --> 01:16:44.089
fight for your fallen brethren...

619
01:16:45.932 --> 01:16:47.627
until the end.

620
01:17:10.154 --> 01:17:11.621
Get up!

621
01:17:15.893 --> 01:17:17.952
Major General Hayashi
is leading an attack.

622
01:17:18.128 --> 01:17:19.720
We are to join him.

623
01:17:23.300 --> 01:17:25.666
Kuribayashi's orders are
to remain in the caves.

624
01:17:28.172 --> 01:17:32.472
Lieutenant Ito says Kuribayashi
is a weak American sympathizer.

625
01:17:42.386 --> 01:17:45.219
We will take back Mt. Suribachi.

626
01:18:07.344 --> 01:18:09.369
Where is Major General Hayashi?

627
01:18:11.949 --> 01:18:13.314
We don't know. sir.

628
01:18:13.951 --> 01:18:15.384
Who is in charge here?

629
01:18:15.619 --> 01:18:17.519
I'm not sure.

630
01:18:20.691 --> 01:18:23.023
Stay here until
I determine the plan of action.

631
01:18:48.785 --> 01:18:50.275
We're dead.

632
01:18:56.260 --> 01:18:58.387
Pull back!

633
01:18:58.929 --> 01:19:00.760
We'll get reinforcements.

634
01:19:33.096 --> 01:19:37.931
Why didn't your regiment join the attack?

635
01:19:41.972 --> 01:19:43.667
Don't sit here like rats!

636
01:19:44.541 --> 01:19:48.136
Come out of your caves and fight!

637
01:19:49.946 --> 01:19:51.504
Where is your commander?

638
01:19:51.682 --> 01:19:53.547
We haven't received the order to attack.

639
01:19:57.220 --> 01:19:59.984
Didn't you receive the order
from General Hayashi?

640
01:20:01.391 --> 01:20:04.485
Kuribayashi countermanded
Hayashi's order.

641
01:20:05.028 --> 01:20:06.962
There is to be no attack.

642
01:20:10.634 --> 01:20:12.795
We will take back Suribachi...

643
01:20:13.737 --> 01:20:15.364
with or without Kuribayashi.

644
01:20:16.073 --> 01:20:19.304
There are already troops on the attack.
Get your men in order.

645
01:20:19.476 --> 01:20:22.104
Lieutenant. may I remind you
of your rank!

646
01:20:22.312 --> 01:20:24.678
Your disrespect for senior officers...

647
01:20:25.515 --> 01:20:28.313
puts your men at needless risk.

648
01:20:30.354 --> 01:20:32.345
I suggest you go back to your cave...

649
01:20:32.522 --> 01:20:36.390
or hand over your men.

650
01:20:46.603 --> 01:20:47.831
Enough.

651
01:20:48.238 --> 01:20:49.967
We'll do it ourselves.

652
01:21:01.084 --> 01:21:02.449
That's against regulations.

653
01:21:02.786 --> 01:21:06.381
That's the officer who tried to kill us.
He doesn't care.

654
01:21:38.555 --> 01:21:39.920
I won't go back.

655
01:21:41.958 --> 01:21:44.153
I've had enough of cave fighting.

656
01:21:46.396 --> 01:21:49.263
You men are now under
Lieutenant Colonel Nishi's command.

657
01:22:01.344 --> 01:22:03.209
I will throw myself under an enemy tank.

658
01:22:06.817 --> 01:22:09.342
I will take out one of their machines.

659
01:22:37.981 --> 01:22:39.209
Hurry.

660
01:22:41.618 --> 01:22:43.017
What is the status?

661
01:22:44.821 --> 01:22:46.550
A thousand men were lost...

662
01:22:46.723 --> 01:22:48.623
in a night attack along Chidori airfield.

663
01:22:48.792 --> 01:22:51.556
Why? I have given them strict orders
not to kill themselves.

664
01:22:51.728 --> 01:22:55.494
It seems that the order to retreat
was not conveyed to all sectors.

665
01:22:56.366 --> 01:22:57.628
Hayashi.

666
01:22:58.134 --> 01:22:59.465
Damn you!

667
01:23:00.537 --> 01:23:02.027
And the American advancement?

668
01:23:02.639 --> 01:23:06.405
A battalion is headed north and we
are fighting back along the west ridge.

669
01:23:06.576 --> 01:23:10.842
Good. Once they cross the west ridge.
they will be surrounded on three sides.

670
01:23:12.249 --> 01:23:13.546
This just arrived.

671
01:23:13.717 --> 01:23:14.843
Read it.

672
01:23:19.823 --> 01:23:21.347
From headquarters...

673
01:23:23.527 --> 01:23:28.191
"We regret that we are unable to send
reinforcements to Iwo at this time.

674
01:23:29.599 --> 01:23:33.091
We earnestly hope you will
fight honorably...

675
01:23:33.870 --> 01:23:36.065
and die for your country."

676
01:25:18.141 --> 01:25:19.233
Bring him in.

677
01:25:35.058 --> 01:25:36.047
Bring him in.

678
01:25:46.503 --> 01:25:48.664
Shall I finish him off?

679
01:25:49.406 --> 01:25:51.397
No. Treat him.

680
01:25:52.842 --> 01:25:54.070
But. sir--

681
01:25:54.244 --> 01:25:56.872
Okubo. you would expect the same.
wouldn't you?

682
01:25:57.047 --> 01:25:58.344
Endo. treat him.

683
01:25:58.748 --> 01:26:01.546
We are low on morphine as it is.

684
01:26:03.019 --> 01:26:05.852
Sir. the Americans would not treat
a wounded Japanese soldier.

685
01:26:06.022 --> 01:26:08.991
Son. have you ever met one?

686
01:26:10.527 --> 01:26:11.653
Treat him.

687
01:26:49.132 --> 01:26:51.225
Where are you. American tanks?

688
01:26:52.302 --> 01:26:53.929
Come and get me!

689
01:27:09.586 --> 01:27:11.213
How is the prisoner doing?

690
01:27:11.721 --> 01:27:13.052
He is awake. sir.

691
01:27:16.993 --> 01:27:20.156
I will question the prisoner
for information.

692
01:29:06.703 --> 01:29:07.931
Damn.

693
01:29:10.306 --> 01:29:11.796
I've had enough of this.

694
01:29:12.542 --> 01:29:14.100
I'm going to surrender.

695
01:29:18.815 --> 01:29:20.749
Go ahead and arrest me.

696
01:29:21.985 --> 01:29:25.751
I don't care anymore. That's what
you were put here for. isn't it?

697
01:29:27.156 --> 01:29:29.624
To report treasonous thoughts.

698
01:29:34.130 --> 01:29:35.927
I was put here because...

699
01:29:37.400 --> 01:29:39.493
I was discharged from the Kempeitai.

700
01:29:42.772 --> 01:29:43.932
Discharged?

701
01:29:48.578 --> 01:29:51.843
I had only been in service
for five days.

702
01:29:55.118 --> 01:29:56.176
Shimizu...

703
01:29:56.352 --> 01:29:59.116
you must always be firm.

704
01:30:00.256 --> 01:30:04.454
Any mercy and people
will take advantage of you.

705
01:30:09.966 --> 01:30:11.126
That's unpatriotic.

706
01:30:11.434 --> 01:30:12.958
Go sort it out. Shimizu.

707
01:30:25.648 --> 01:30:28.481
You do not have the Imperial flag
properly displayed.

708
01:30:28.651 --> 01:30:29.879
I'm sorry.

709
01:30:30.053 --> 01:30:33.580
My husband has gone to war
and I couldn't put it up myself.

710
01:30:33.756 --> 01:30:36.452
It is unpatriotic
not to have the flag displayed.

711
01:30:36.626 --> 01:30:38.890
If you help me. I'll put it up now.

712
01:30:59.415 --> 01:31:01.349
Get that dog to shut up.

713
01:31:02.919 --> 01:31:04.113
What was that. sir?

714
01:31:05.254 --> 01:31:09.520
That dog is a nuisance.
It is disruptive of Army communications.

715
01:31:10.093 --> 01:31:12.152
I am very sorry. sir.

716
01:31:18.534 --> 01:31:20.627
Shimizu. Dispose of the dog.

717
01:31:21.938 --> 01:31:25.499
We can't have a dog interfering
with important military commands.

718
01:31:31.280 --> 01:31:32.907
Take the dog in the back.

719
01:31:33.249 --> 01:31:34.614
It's only a dog.

720
01:31:34.851 --> 01:31:37.411
It won't happen again.

721
01:31:37.887 --> 01:31:39.286
Take it out back.

722
01:31:39.789 --> 01:31:41.450
Keep the children inside.

723
01:31:42.625 --> 01:31:43.887
Hurry up.

724
01:32:32.208 --> 01:32:34.506
Take the dog into the house
and keep him quiet...

725
01:32:35.244 --> 01:32:36.233
and never let him out.

726
01:32:48.424 --> 01:32:49.948
It's taken care of. sir.

727
01:33:28.331 --> 01:33:30.231
Are you trying to make a fool out of me?

728
01:33:32.101 --> 01:33:37.403
If you can't even shoot a dog.
you'll never be able to handle the Reds.

729
01:33:39.175 --> 01:33:40.574
You are unpatriotic!

730
01:33:46.816 --> 01:33:49.182
I was discharged for insubordination...

731
01:33:50.386 --> 01:33:52.081
and sent here.

732
01:34:00.897 --> 01:34:02.660
Don't look so glum. Shimizu.

733
01:34:04.200 --> 01:34:06.828
At least now only the enemy hates you.

734
01:34:11.941 --> 01:34:13.704
I don't blame the dog.

735
01:34:39.468 --> 01:34:40.628
Taro...

736
01:34:41.070 --> 01:34:43.971
tonight I attended my farewell party.

737
01:34:44.607 --> 01:34:47.132
The wives also attended.
so there was a lot of fuss.

738
01:34:47.310 --> 01:34:50.245
Greeting all the ladies...

739
01:34:50.479 --> 01:34:53.607
kept me from enjoying the food.

740
01:37:38.714 --> 01:37:40.739
Is there any information
of the enemy's plan?

741
01:37:41.550 --> 01:37:43.745
No. it's just a letter.

742
01:37:45.621 --> 01:37:47.418
It's from his mother.

743
01:37:49.892 --> 01:37:50.950
"Sam...

744
01:37:51.994 --> 01:37:54.360
I have mailed you
a couple of books to read.

745
01:37:54.964 --> 01:37:56.488
I hope that you like them.

746
01:37:57.900 --> 01:37:58.889
Yesterday...

747
01:37:59.635 --> 01:38:04.402
the dogs dug a hole under the fence.

748
01:38:05.775 --> 01:38:10.007
They ran all over the neighborhood.

749
01:38:11.113 --> 01:38:13.308
By the time we found them...

750
01:38:14.517 --> 01:38:19.511
the Harrisons' roosters were terrorized.

751
01:38:20.322 --> 01:38:23.155
Don't worry about us.

752
01:38:24.427 --> 01:38:28.488
Just take care of yourself
and come back safely.

753
01:38:28.864 --> 01:38:32.595
Remember what I said to you...

754
01:38:36.205 --> 01:38:37.832
always do what is right...

755
01:38:38.941 --> 01:38:41.136
because it is right.

756
01:38:42.311 --> 01:38:45.974
I pray for a speedy end to the war...

757
01:38:46.148 --> 01:38:47.547
and your safe return.

758
01:38:49.151 --> 01:38:50.482
Love. Mom."

759
01:39:25.154 --> 01:39:27.748
I'm sorry. sir. There is no more medicine.

760
01:39:27.923 --> 01:39:31.086
It's all right. I'm useless now.
Go help the others!

761
01:41:02.451 --> 01:41:04.476
Okubo. come here.

762
01:41:11.193 --> 01:41:12.956
How are we on ammunition?

763
01:41:15.030 --> 01:41:17.464
Not good. sir.

764
01:41:19.001 --> 01:41:20.969
Our mortars have been taken out...

765
01:41:21.770 --> 01:41:23.635
and we're out of machine gun ammo.

766
01:41:25.441 --> 01:41:28.774
We have only our rifles.

767
01:41:30.846 --> 01:41:31.835
Okubo...

768
01:41:32.014 --> 01:41:35.814
you are now in charge of the men.

769
01:41:40.556 --> 01:41:42.148
We can no longer hold this area.

770
01:41:42.891 --> 01:41:46.383
You must guide
the rest of the men north.

771
01:41:49.064 --> 01:41:52.465
Take whatever food and ammo
we have left.

772
01:41:53.636 --> 01:41:56.002
What about you. sir?

773
01:41:59.408 --> 01:42:02.844
I'm tired of sharing this cave
with all of you.

774
01:42:03.679 --> 01:42:06.204
I'm a one-man show from here on out.

775
01:42:06.548 --> 01:42:08.311
What are you talking about. sir?

776
01:42:09.685 --> 01:42:12.984
Your first order of business...

777
01:42:14.023 --> 01:42:15.752
is to find some water.

778
01:42:42.751 --> 01:42:43.911
Men...

779
01:42:45.387 --> 01:42:47.014
do your best.

780
01:42:48.524 --> 01:42:52.927
Do what is right...

781
01:42:54.763 --> 01:42:57.027
because it is right.

782
01:42:59.201 --> 01:43:00.429
Understood?

783
01:43:08.243 --> 01:43:13.203
I will make sure that they send you
medicine and food.

784
01:43:15.451 --> 01:43:16.782
It has been a great honor...

785
01:43:18.220 --> 01:43:19.448
to serve...

786
01:43:20.756 --> 01:43:22.223
under you.

787
01:44:01.363 --> 01:44:02.921
Hand me my rifle.

788
01:44:26.722 --> 01:44:28.622
I'm sorry. Okubo.

789
01:45:48.737 --> 01:45:51.934
Why am I not getting any reports?
Have we heard from Admiral Ichimaru?

790
01:45:52.107 --> 01:45:54.871
- No. sir.
- What about Nishi or Hayashi?

791
01:45:57.312 --> 01:46:00.372
- Send out messengers!
- We have. Many times.

792
01:46:00.616 --> 01:46:02.345
None of them have come back.

793
01:46:02.851 --> 01:46:04.614
You can't plan strategy like this!

794
01:46:15.797 --> 01:46:19.289
I have been thinking about
what Lt. Colonel Nishi said.

795
01:46:20.068 --> 01:46:21.467
He's right.

796
01:46:26.742 --> 01:46:29.643
I don't know anything about the enemy.

797
01:46:30.412 --> 01:46:34.075
I believed that the Americans
were cowards...

798
01:46:40.222 --> 01:46:41.985
but they weren't.

799
01:46:47.229 --> 01:46:49.390
I was taught...

800
01:46:51.033 --> 01:46:52.762
that they were savages...

801
01:46:54.569 --> 01:46:56.537
but that American soldier...

802
01:47:04.046 --> 01:47:06.173
his mother's words...

803
01:47:10.118 --> 01:47:12.245
were the same as my mother's.

804
01:47:13.455 --> 01:47:17.448
I want to fulfill my duty
for the general...

805
01:47:18.360 --> 01:47:20.521
and our country...

806
01:47:22.264 --> 01:47:24.391
but I don't want to die for nothing.

807
01:47:30.405 --> 01:47:31.770
What do you think?

808
01:47:43.986 --> 01:47:45.078
You...

809
01:47:46.388 --> 01:47:49.152
haven't lived enough to realize...

810
01:47:53.996 --> 01:47:56.464
what you are sacrificing.

811
01:48:04.806 --> 01:48:07.001
Will you surrender with me?

812
01:48:28.430 --> 01:48:29.761
Careful.

813
01:48:33.368 --> 01:48:37.168
They'll notice if we leave together.
You go first.

814
01:48:38.140 --> 01:48:39.903
I'll make up an excuse.

815
01:48:40.075 --> 01:48:42.703
After a while. I'll tell them
I'm going to check on you.

816
01:48:42.878 --> 01:48:44.869
We'll be gone before they even notice.

817
01:48:48.283 --> 01:48:50.308
Pretend that you have dysentery.

818
01:48:51.153 --> 01:48:53.383
Give me your dysentery look.

819
01:49:03.331 --> 01:49:04.992
I guess that'll have to do.

820
01:49:13.975 --> 01:49:15.533
Where are you going?

821
01:49:15.877 --> 01:49:17.504
I've got dysentery.

822
01:49:17.979 --> 01:49:19.913
You're going to surrender. aren't you?

823
01:49:20.082 --> 01:49:22.175
If you are. take me with you.

824
01:49:22.818 --> 01:49:25.412
- I've had enough of this war.
- Be quiet!

825
01:49:33.895 --> 01:49:36.386
Where are you going?

826
01:49:36.631 --> 01:49:39.099
He said he wasn't feeling well.
It could be dysentery.

827
01:49:39.267 --> 01:49:40.529
You two! Stop!

828
01:49:46.308 --> 01:49:47.605
Sir. maybe they got spooked.

829
01:50:04.893 --> 01:50:07.361
Miura. you're on guard.

830
01:50:08.029 --> 01:50:10.020
Make sure we have no more deserters.

831
01:51:36.318 --> 01:51:37.945
What unit were you with?

832
01:51:40.789 --> 01:51:44.691
Higashiyama 314th.

833
01:51:54.402 --> 01:51:55.835
Did you hear...

834
01:51:57.539 --> 01:52:01.134
I heard that they would give you a meal.

835
01:52:03.144 --> 01:52:04.372
A meal...

836
01:52:08.550 --> 01:52:10.245
That sounds good.

837
01:52:15.257 --> 01:52:16.918
I'm from Yokohama. too.

838
01:52:20.362 --> 01:52:23.661
After this is over. you can come visit me.

839
01:53:39.974 --> 01:53:41.168
Lieutenant!

840
01:54:22.817 --> 01:54:24.614
Let this be a lesson to anyone else...

841
01:54:26.855 --> 01:54:28.482
who wants to surrender.

842
01:55:41.396 --> 01:55:45.264
We need to get through the crossfire
to reach the north...

843
01:55:46.134 --> 01:55:47.829
and join our forces at the front.

844
01:55:53.875 --> 01:55:54.967
Listen.

845
01:55:56.044 --> 01:55:58.535
We'll head for that cave
and make our way from there.

846
01:56:02.083 --> 01:56:03.641
Don't waste a bullet!

847
01:56:04.819 --> 01:56:06.252
Not a single one.

848
01:56:06.821 --> 01:56:08.379
Don't shoot recklessly.

849
01:57:09.050 --> 01:57:13.111
These are Nishi's troops
and the survivors from Suribachi.

850
01:57:17.225 --> 01:57:19.193
Are there no officers?

851
01:57:23.031 --> 01:57:25.295
You all did a good job making it here.

852
01:57:26.367 --> 01:57:28.028
Fujita. water for them.

853
01:57:32.674 --> 01:57:35.575
I'm sorry. sir. There is no more water.

854
01:57:39.414 --> 01:57:40.506
I'm sorry.

855
01:57:41.849 --> 01:57:43.180
At least you can rest.

856
01:57:58.366 --> 01:57:59.993
You look familiar.

857
01:58:05.239 --> 01:58:06.831
You almost lost your head.

858
01:58:09.877 --> 01:58:13.938
That was the second time you saved me.

859
01:58:16.751 --> 01:58:18.184
The first time...

860
01:58:18.886 --> 01:58:22.515
was the day you landed on the island.

861
01:58:26.294 --> 01:58:28.228
Of course. I remember.

862
01:58:29.897 --> 01:58:31.524
Well. everything happens in threes.

863
01:58:48.216 --> 01:58:49.547
Hanako...

864
01:58:50.585 --> 01:58:52.985
This letter will probably
never get to you...

865
01:58:53.721 --> 01:58:54.710
but...

866
01:58:55.423 --> 01:58:57.653
it comforts me to write.

867
01:58:59.127 --> 01:59:01.652
For five days. we've been
without water and food.

868
01:59:02.964 --> 01:59:04.727
To survive...

869
01:59:06.501 --> 01:59:08.560
we do unspeakable things.

870
01:59:11.572 --> 01:59:13.403
There is no escape now.

871
01:59:14.175 --> 01:59:15.335
But...

872
01:59:16.577 --> 01:59:19.410
my only concern is for you and the baby.

873
01:59:25.953 --> 01:59:27.511
Dig up some worms.

874
01:59:46.607 --> 01:59:49.303
The battle is approaching its end...

875
01:59:49.877 --> 01:59:52.607
and there is no more ammunition.
no more water.

876
01:59:52.780 --> 01:59:56.272
All the survivors will engage
in a general attack.

877
01:59:57.618 --> 02:00:01.054
I pray for the victory
and safety of the Empire.

878
02:00:01.656 --> 02:00:03.783
I bid you farewell.

879
02:00:05.460 --> 02:00:09.521
For the country.
I could not fulfill all of my duties.

880
02:00:09.697 --> 02:00:13.633
Now that we have no ammunition.
it is with regret that we must perish.

881
02:00:20.141 --> 02:00:23.304
You made it all the way from Suribachi?

882
02:00:26.214 --> 02:00:28.409
That must have been quite a journey.

883
02:00:34.155 --> 02:00:35.747
You are quite a soldier.

884
02:00:38.092 --> 02:00:39.491
No. sir.

885
02:00:40.561 --> 02:00:41.892
I'm just a simple baker.

886
02:00:42.697 --> 02:00:44.494
You were a baker?

887
02:00:46.000 --> 02:00:47.058
Any family?

888
02:00:48.102 --> 02:00:49.399
A wife...

889
02:00:50.004 --> 02:00:54.566
and a baby girl born
last summer in Ohmiya.

890
02:00:58.045 --> 02:00:59.672
I haven't met her yet.

891
02:01:05.953 --> 02:01:07.352
It's strange.

892
02:01:09.924 --> 02:01:13.451
I promised myself to fight
until death for my family...

893
02:01:15.363 --> 02:01:19.697
but the thought of my family
makes it difficult to keep that promise.

894
02:01:43.090 --> 02:01:45.058
A radio transmission from the homeland.

895
02:01:58.739 --> 02:02:00.206
For General Kuribayashi...

896
02:02:00.374 --> 02:02:04.743
and his troops. who are fighting bravely
for our country...

897
02:02:04.912 --> 02:02:09.508
a song will be sung by the children of
Nagano. which is Kuribayashi's hometown.

898
02:02:09.851 --> 02:02:13.981
On the waves of the Pacific

899
02:02:14.155 --> 02:02:17.420
down south from the Imperial City

900
02:02:17.959 --> 02:02:22.623
a small lonely island floats

901
02:02:26.033 --> 02:02:29.662
The fate of our Imperial country

902
02:02:29.837 --> 02:02:34.501
lies in the hands of this island

903
02:02:37.311 --> 02:02:39.939
Iwo Jima

904
02:02:43.484 --> 02:02:46.976
As long as we stand

905
02:02:47.455 --> 02:02:51.551
we shall feel safe. as the Imperial land

906
02:02:51.726 --> 02:02:56.390
shall forever be at peace

907
02:02:59.667 --> 02:03:04.331
We shall fight with pride
and honor at any price

908
02:03:06.741 --> 02:03:10.302
Our proud island

909
02:03:10.912 --> 02:03:13.574
Iwo Jima

910
02:03:35.903 --> 02:03:37.234
Do me a favor.

911
02:03:38.906 --> 02:03:42.672
Stay here and burn all these documents.
and my military chest.

912
02:03:43.844 --> 02:03:46.005
Everything happens in threes.

913
02:04:15.476 --> 02:04:17.501
We will make a general attack.

914
02:04:18.579 --> 02:04:20.911
Although Japan has lost...

915
02:04:21.649 --> 02:04:23.514
one day...

916
02:04:24.385 --> 02:04:26.512
our people will praise your dedication.

917
02:04:27.655 --> 02:04:31.682
A day will come when they
will weep and pray for your souls.

918
02:04:34.395 --> 02:04:36.693
Be proud to die for your country.

919
02:04:43.838 --> 02:04:46.329
I will always be in front of you.

920
02:07:28.969 --> 02:07:30.197
No more.

921
02:07:32.406 --> 02:07:33.395
No more.

922
02:07:41.482 --> 02:07:43.177
Thank you. Fujita.

923
02:08:15.316 --> 02:08:16.476
This is an order.

924
02:09:24.952 --> 02:09:26.146
You again.

925
02:09:29.623 --> 02:09:33.389
I have one more favor to ask of you.

926
02:09:35.462 --> 02:09:36.656
Bury me...

927
02:09:37.798 --> 02:09:39.789
so that no one will find me.

928
02:09:54.381 --> 02:09:55.370
Taro...

929
02:09:55.816 --> 02:09:57.249
I will be home soon.

930
02:09:58.519 --> 02:10:00.510
I'm glad to be going back to Japan...

931
02:10:01.488 --> 02:10:04.889
but I'm a bit sad
to leave my friends behind.

932
02:10:08.362 --> 02:10:09.920
I drove home...

933
02:10:11.065 --> 02:10:12.054
but...

934
02:10:12.499 --> 02:10:15.093
it's lonely driving all by myself.

935
02:10:27.548 --> 02:10:29.539
Is this still Japanese soil?

936
02:10:39.059 --> 02:10:40.788
This is still Japan.

937
02:14:01.728 --> 02:14:03.093
Be careful.

